<?xml version="1.0"?>
<Fleet xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
  <Name>bgy-s2h bombers</Name>
  <Version>3</Version>
  <TotalPoints>3000</TotalPoints>
  <FactionKey>Stock/Alliance</FactionKey>
  <Description>Difficulty: &lt;color=green&gt;easy tbh&lt;/color&gt;

sprinter bombers. formation LOOSE, speed FLANK, movement order straight to orbit then straight down enemy backline. chaff on 1 and 5, total of five blankets with one hangup, plus a pinard for not getting offset tracked. don't get spotted, don't get locked, don't get killed (even though for once, i do actually have dc). salvo size 2, use mixed salvos as below. i have 3 rebounds, so a couple rockets can get hardkilled, but otherwise... just softkill bro. remember to lock everything. its cmd. obvs

missiles (to be used in mixed salvos):
223- HEI 1
224- HEI 2
233- HEKP 1
234- HEKP 2
244- anti-pike ACM (launch with z prio)
1- arming missile

fluff: all the names are references to a certain character, except for the eyepoker (244). fleet is directly inspired by my oshi iris and his sprinter bombers. his and my fleet do the same thing, so if you're unfortunate enough to want to use them, just take your pick. he always says his is better :( anyways... this worked when i tested it against SCCC, worked when i tested it in IMA and EMT inhouses, and worked when i drove into pub stacks. so... have fun?
  </Description>
